olive oil
1 eggplant
1 Brown Onion
2 clove garlic
1 packet diced bacon
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
2 cup water
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Chargrilled Capsicum Relish
20 g butter
1 pinch chilli flakes
2 packet Israeli couscous
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
1 courgette
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Cut eggplant into small chunks. Slice courgette into thick half-moons. Roughly chop onion. Finely chop garlic.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook diced bacon and onion, breaking up with a spoon, until tender and golden, 5-6 minutes.
• Add garlic and garlic & herb seasoning and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add Israeli couscous, vegetable stock powder and the water. Stir to combine.

• Transfer risotto to a baking dish. Cover tightly with foil and bake until liquid is absorbed and rice is ‘al dente’, 24-28 minutes.

• Meanwhile, place eggplant and courgette on a lined oven tray.
• Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Remove risotto from oven, then stir through baby spinach leaves, grated Parmesan cheese, chargrilled capsicum relish, roasted veggies and the butter.
• Stir through a splash of water to loosen risotto if needed.

• Divide roasted eggplant, bacon and veggie risotto between bowls.
• Garnish with chilli flakes (if using) to serve. Enjoy!